==Aftermath==
Transvaal and Kimberley remained the only sides to contest the Currie Cup in the following season, and in their 1891 match, Kimberley won by 58 runs in a [[Glossary of cricket terms#T|timeless match]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/3/3660.html |title=Transvaal v Kimberley: Currie Cup 1890/91 |publisher=CricketArchive |accessdate=19 January 2013}}</ref> The tournament was not played in 1891<U+2013>92, but when it restarted the following year, a third team, [[Western Province cricket team (South Africa)|Western Province]] joined, while Kimberley were renamed Griqualand West.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Events/3/Currie_Cup_1892-93.html |title=Currie Cup 1892/93 |publisher=CricketArchive |accessdate=19 January 2013}}</ref>

